3
00:00:17,280 --> 00:00:21,000

4
00:00:21,000 --> 00:00:25,350

5
00:00:25,350 --> 00:00:29,490

6
00:00:29,490 --> 00:00:33,310

7
00:00:33,310 --> 00:00:38,340

8
00:00:42,130 --> 00:00:45,400

9
00:00:45,400 --> 00:00:50,120

10
00:00:52,699 --> 00:00:55,299
 There's a buyer for the place you're staying in.

11
00:00:55,299 --> 00:00:56,699
 They said that, if they can move in immediately,

12
00:00:56,699 --> 00:00:59,733
 they'll pay more than the market price.

13
00:01:00,599 --> 00:01:02,767
You'll have to move soon.

14
00:01:02,767 --> 00:01:05,333
Where will you go this time?

15
00:01:05,333 --> 00:01:08,164
No, I'm not moving.

16
00:01:08,164 --> 00:01:09,466
Why not?

17
00:01:09,466 --> 00:01:11,431
I'm not going to sell this place.

18
00:01:11,431 --> 00:01:13,565
I'm going to stay here.

19
00:01:13,565 --> 00:01:15,632
You said it was a temporary stay for profit...

20
00:01:15,632 --> 00:01:17,466
Yes, I said that.

21
00:01:17,466 --> 00:01:20,234
That a place is a means to increase your assets.

22
00:01:20,234 --> 00:01:22,333
But now, it's not.

23
00:01:24,966 --> 00:01:28,533
To me, this isn't just a place,

24
00:01:29,634 --> 00:01:31,120
but it's also a home.

25
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:35,400

26
00:01:36,032 --> 00:01:37,498
I've been meaning to ask you.

27
00:01:37,498 --> 00:01:40,932
Can you accompany me somewhere?

28
00:01:42,230 --> 00:01:44,460

29
00:01:44,460 --> 00:01:45,699
You know what?

30
00:01:45,699 --> 00:01:50,832
It's been ten years since I last wrote a moving-in notification.

31
00:01:50,832 --> 00:01:52,331
Then how did you live all this time?

32
00:01:52,331 --> 00:01:55,465
I lived in empty places owned by the investment company,

33
00:01:55,465 --> 00:01:58,766
so I never stayed in one place longer than a week.

34
00:01:58,766 --> 00:02:01,299
I didn't know you moved so often.

35
00:02:01,299 --> 00:02:06,032
After I met you, I realized for the first time that I was homeless.

36
00:02:06,032 --> 00:02:11,332
You said that a home is a container that holds life.

37
00:02:11,332 --> 00:02:14,332
I had a lot of residences,

38
00:02:14,332 --> 00:02:16,900
but I had no home.

39
00:02:17,733 --> 00:02:21,500
I'm going to keep living in this house which holds a lot of our memories.

40
00:02:21,500 --> 00:02:24,167
While making even better memories.

41
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:31,032
- Are you done? 
 - Yes.

42
00:02:32,130 --> 00:02:35,560

43
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:38,580

44
00:02:38,580 --> 00:02:39,833
Editor Na.

45
00:02:39,833 --> 00:02:42,331
How's your article linking up with Editor Nam's?

46
00:02:42,331 --> 00:02:45,566
Oh, I have some stuff I need to organize.

47
00:02:45,566 --> 00:02:47,031
I'll hand it over to Editor Na soon.

48
00:02:47,031 --> 00:02:52,799
How about we change the theme and go with what a good house to live in is?

49
00:02:52,799 --> 00:02:54,331
Yes, sounds good.

50
00:02:54,331 --> 00:02:56,331
Okay, then. Carry on with that.

51
00:02:56,331 --> 00:02:58,366
What is this issue's travel theme?

52
00:02:58,366 --> 00:03:00,399
How about a special on a school trip?

53
00:03:00,399 --> 00:03:03,531
So people can be reminded of their school trip.

54
00:03:03,531 --> 00:03:06,298
Wow, that's good.

55
00:03:06,298 --> 00:03:08,466
- In my day, we went to Gyeongju. 
 - Me, too.

56
00:03:08,466 --> 00:03:09,567
You, too? Me, too.

57
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:13,367
Yes, Gyeongju is the best for school trips.

58
00:03:16,900 --> 00:03:19,766
Did you go to another place for your school trip?

59
00:03:19,766 --> 00:03:20,732
Yes.

60
00:03:20,732 --> 00:03:22,999
- Where? 
 - The convenience store.

61
00:03:22,999 --> 00:03:24,231
What?

62
00:03:24,231 --> 00:03:25,732
I always worked part-time at night.

63
00:03:25,732 --> 00:03:28,533
So I haven't been on a school trip.

64
00:03:31,100 --> 00:03:33,131
But now that you're financially capable,

65
00:03:33,132 --> 00:03:35,933
you must've been to every travel destination.

66
00:03:35,933 --> 00:03:37,131
No.

67
00:03:37,132 --> 00:03:40,932
I've been all over the country for a survey,

68
00:03:40,932 --> 00:03:43,966
but I've never been on a trip.

69
00:03:43,966 --> 00:03:45,499
Excuse me. I have to take this.

70
00:03:45,499 --> 00:03:46,899
Yes, Secretary Hwang?

71
00:03:46,899 --> 00:03:49,832
How did the investment in Sangeon Construction go?

72
00:03:49,832 --> 00:03:51,165
Really?

73
00:03:51,166 --> 00:03:52,499
From when?

74
00:03:52,499 --> 00:03:55,700
In a way, I feel bad for CEO Yoo.

75
00:03:55,700 --> 00:03:59,534
He doesn't know what fun there is in life.

76
00:04:02,066 --> 00:04:03,366
What?

77
00:04:03,366 --> 00:04:04,732
A trip?

78
00:04:04,732 --> 00:04:06,964
You said you've never been on a school trip.

79
00:04:06,964 --> 00:04:09,266
Let's go on a school trip this weekend.

80
00:04:09,266 --> 00:04:11,166
To Gyeongju.

81
00:04:12,966 --> 00:04:14,599
What's wrong?

82
00:04:15,300 --> 00:04:16,999
Are you sick?

83
00:04:16,999 --> 00:04:18,399
No.

84
00:04:18,399 --> 00:04:23,265
Thinking about going on a trip with you is making my heart flutter already.

85
00:04:25,432 --> 00:04:27,932
- Great. Let's go on a trip. 
 - Good.

86
00:04:27,932 --> 00:04:30,164
Have you gone on a lot of trips?

87
00:04:30,164 --> 00:04:32,499
When was your last trip?

88
00:04:32,499 --> 00:04:34,164
A school trip.

89
00:04:34,164 --> 00:04:35,100
What?

90
00:04:35,100 --> 00:04:38,865
You must know since you saw my post on the café,

91
00:04:38,865 --> 00:04:40,898
but my family suddenly became poor,

92
00:04:40,898 --> 00:04:43,790
so I never dreamed of going on a trip after that.

93
00:04:43,790 --> 00:04:47,290

94
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:48,666
 Is this really it?

95
00:04:48,666 --> 00:04:51,265
 Yes. This is now our home.

96
00:04:51,265 --> 00:04:52,633
 Awesome.

97
00:04:52,633 --> 00:04:56,865
 Through my father's friend, we bought an unsold unit at a cheap price,

98
00:04:56,865 --> 00:05:01,633
 and my parents finally became homeowners.

99
00:05:02,399 --> 00:05:03,766
 Who are you?

100
00:05:03,766 --> 00:05:04,699
 Who are you?

101
00:05:04,700 --> 00:05:06,164
 I'm the owner of this house.

102
00:05:06,165 --> 00:05:08,798
 We're supposed to move in here today.

103
00:05:08,798 --> 00:05:10,264
 What are you talking about? I live here.

104
00:05:10,265 --> 00:05:11,232
 What a weird person!

105
00:05:11,233 --> 00:05:14,632
 It turned out to be a Double Contract fraud.

106
00:05:16,299 --> 00:05:21,999
 My parents lost all their money and the money they borrowed.

107
00:05:33,600 --> 00:05:35,466
 Let's go.

108
00:05:47,165 --> 00:05:48,833
 Mom.

109
00:05:53,467 --> 00:05:55,199
 Honey.

110
00:05:55,200 --> 00:05:56,499
 Young Won.

111
00:05:56,499 --> 00:05:58,299
 I'll make money and return.

112
00:05:58,299 --> 00:05:59,931
 I'm so sorry.

113
00:05:59,931 --> 00:06:05,833
 My father disappeared like that, and my mom and I lived a hard life.

114
00:06:09,666 --> 00:06:12,965
So that's why you said you moved often.

115
00:06:12,965 --> 00:06:14,766
Yes.

116
00:06:16,032 --> 00:06:22,300
Since I was busy making ends meet, I couldn't think of going on a trip.

117
00:06:24,032 --> 00:06:25,734
Let's go on that trip.

118
00:06:25,734 --> 00:06:27,031
Yes.

119
00:06:27,031 --> 00:06:30,466
Let's forget the past pain and have a great time.

120
00:06:30,466 --> 00:06:32,700
Okay.

121
00:06:32,700 --> 00:06:34,599
Oh, wait.

122
00:06:35,967 --> 00:06:38,633
My heart is fluttering...

123
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:40,866
A class reunion?

124
00:06:40,866 --> 00:06:43,232
Oh, no. I don't think I can go.

125
00:06:43,232 --> 00:06:45,931
I'm going on a trip this weekend.

126
00:06:45,931 --> 00:06:47,366
What?

127
00:06:47,366 --> 00:06:49,899
Yes, with my boyfriend.

128
00:06:49,899 --> 00:06:51,999
I'm sorry.

129
00:06:51,999 --> 00:06:53,366
Bye.

130
00:06:53,366 --> 00:06:55,566
Are you going on a trip? With Hyung?

131
00:06:55,566 --> 00:06:58,400
Oh, yes.

132
00:06:58,400 --> 00:07:00,366
Thanks.

133
00:07:02,432 --> 00:07:05,731
It's incredible that Hyung is going on a trip.

134
00:07:05,731 --> 00:07:09,665
He used to say that if he had time for a trip, he'd rather earn money.

135
00:07:09,665 --> 00:07:13,366
Indeed, the power of love is strong.

136
00:07:16,867 --> 00:07:20,499
Hyung has changed a lot after meeting you.

137
00:07:20,499 --> 00:07:22,965
Seeing how he's getting along well with people.

138
00:07:22,965 --> 00:07:27,299
He usually never opened up to anyone.

139
00:07:28,566 --> 00:07:31,500
It's because of that person, right?

140
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:33,599
When he was betrayed by someone he trusted.

141
00:07:33,599 --> 00:07:35,967
I guess you knew.

142
00:07:35,967 --> 00:07:38,732
After that, he built a wall around himself

143
00:07:38,732 --> 00:07:41,200
and lived a lonely life,

144
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:43,733
only focused on making money.

145
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:47,465
Hyung being able to smile like that now,

146
00:07:47,465 --> 00:07:49,933
it's all thanks to you.

147
00:07:50,566 --> 00:07:54,234
Please make lots of good memories on your trip, too.

148
00:07:54,234 --> 00:07:55,967
Okay.

149
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,199
- Ui Joo Ui Joo. 
 - Yeah?

150
00:08:13,199 --> 00:08:16,499
- I can sleep over tonight again, right? 
 - Again?

151
00:08:16,499 --> 00:08:18,765
Won't your parents worry?

152
00:08:18,766 --> 00:08:21,199
I told them I'm working overtime.

153
00:08:21,199 --> 00:08:24,733
I love hanging out with you all day.

154
00:08:24,734 --> 00:08:27,331
Which brings me to my question. What if we get married?

155
00:08:27,331 --> 00:08:28,531
No.

156
00:08:28,532 --> 00:08:31,632
I told you I don't ever plan on getting married.

157
00:08:31,632 --> 00:08:34,899
Don't reject the idea right away...

158
00:08:34,900 --> 00:08:36,865
Seriously!

159
00:08:36,865 --> 00:08:37,965
I told you.

160
00:08:37,966 --> 00:08:39,999
If you want to get married, date someone else!

161
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:42,267
I'll let you go!

162
00:08:42,267 --> 00:08:43,332
Okay.

163
00:08:43,333 --> 00:08:44,200
I take back what I said.

164
00:08:44,200 --> 00:08:46,933
Starting today, I'm against marriage!

165
00:08:46,934 --> 00:08:48,600
Marriage? I loathe it!

166
00:08:48,600 --> 00:08:52,231
Let's date each other our whole lives.

167
00:08:52,232 --> 00:08:54,765
Ui Joo Ui Joo.

168
00:08:55,667 --> 00:08:58,332
Hold my hands now.

169
00:08:58,332 --> 00:08:59,732
Instead of yoga, let's do another workout.

170
00:08:59,732 --> 00:09:01,566
Another workout?

171
00:09:08,900 --> 00:09:10,800
Come on.

172
00:09:13,466 --> 00:09:14,332
Yes!

173
00:09:14,333 --> 00:09:16,932
Ui Joo Ui Joo!

174
00:09:16,932 --> 00:09:19,266
♪ Let's go to a place where you can ♪

175
00:09:19,266 --> 00:09:23,164
♪ Hear echoes in the flowing stream ♪

176
00:09:23,164 --> 00:09:25,331
♪ To that place ♪

177
00:09:25,331 --> 00:09:26,667
♪ Let's go on a trip ♪

178
00:09:26,667 --> 00:09:27,965
And do what?

179
00:09:27,965 --> 00:09:30,598
What do you do on a trip?

180
00:09:30,599 --> 00:09:33,065
I've never been on one.

181
00:09:40,299 --> 00:09:43,400
I'm going on a trip with Ja Sung.

182
00:09:43,400 --> 00:09:45,866
I can't believe this.

183
00:09:50,332 --> 00:09:52,633

184
00:09:52,633 --> 00:09:55,999

185
00:10:23,734 --> 00:10:26,332
Hello? Editor Nam.

186
00:10:26,332 --> 00:10:29,000
Where is this person right now?

187
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:37,999
Could it really be your father?

188
00:10:37,999 --> 00:10:39,665
You saw the photo yourself.

189
00:10:39,666 --> 00:10:41,131
It's definitely him.

190
00:10:41,131 --> 00:10:42,699
Yes.

191
00:10:42,699 --> 00:10:44,932
I hope it is.

192
00:10:46,367 --> 00:10:47,733
I think it's over there.

193
00:10:47,734 --> 00:10:50,167
Yes, I think we're almost there.

194
00:10:59,232 --> 00:11:01,032
Dad?

195
00:11:03,299 --> 00:11:05,399
Dad!

196
00:11:06,934 --> 00:11:08,800
Young Won!

197
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,832
Honey!

198
00:11:34,232 --> 00:11:35,598
- You! 
 - Ouch, ouch!

199
00:11:35,598 --> 00:11:37,633
- You should've died! 
 - I'm sorry, Honey.

200
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:39,199
- You should've died! 
 - Please forgive me!

201
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:41,532
- Stop it. 
 - Because of you, Young Won and I

202
00:11:41,533 --> 00:11:44,933
went through so much hardship!

203
00:11:51,265 --> 00:11:52,799
Dad!

204
00:11:52,799 --> 00:11:54,399
Stop!

205
00:11:54,400 --> 00:11:56,131
Let go of me!

206
00:11:56,132 --> 00:11:57,832
Honey!

207
00:12:03,232 --> 00:12:05,233
Honey!

208
00:12:05,233 --> 00:12:07,067
I'm sorry!

209
00:12:08,365 --> 00:12:11,332
 Something came up at home, so I put in a leave.

210
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:14,399
 It's nothing bad so don't worry.

211
00:12:14,399 --> 00:12:16,799
 I'll call you later.

212
00:12:21,232 --> 00:12:25,165
 What do you want to eat at Gyeongju...?

213
00:12:25,166 --> 00:12:26,431
No.

214
00:12:26,432 --> 00:12:30,566
She's away due to a family matter. I shouldn't bother her.

215
00:12:35,065 --> 00:12:38,434
What in the world should we do on the trip?

216
00:12:55,832 --> 00:12:58,800
Editor Nam. How's the Gyeongju travel article going?

217
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:01,832
- Sir? 
 - As the editor in charge, please tell me.

218
00:13:01,833 --> 00:13:05,531
What's a must-see place in Gyeongju?

219
00:13:05,531 --> 00:13:09,231
This is random. Oh, are you going on a trip to Gyeongju?

220
00:13:09,232 --> 00:13:11,267
Oh, no.

221
00:13:11,267 --> 00:13:12,699
I'm the CEO of this magazine,

222
00:13:12,700 --> 00:13:16,531
but I feel like I've only been focused on my promo articles.

223
00:13:16,531 --> 00:13:18,733
So I'm thinking of pouring interest into other segments.

224
00:13:18,734 --> 00:13:21,298
Wow, you're amazing. Even when you're so busy—

225
00:13:21,298 --> 00:13:23,264
So please tell me, Editor Nam.

226
00:13:23,265 --> 00:13:26,434
What's a must-see place in Gyeongju?

227
00:13:26,434 --> 00:13:29,065
Museums and historic sites are a given.

228
00:13:29,065 --> 00:13:32,566
If I were to recommend something else... Hwangridan Road.

229
00:13:32,566 --> 00:13:34,598
Wow, Hwangridan Road is amazing.

230
00:13:34,599 --> 00:13:35,899
I went there with my wife, too.

231
00:13:35,899 --> 00:13:37,767
You did? What did you do there?

232
00:13:37,767 --> 00:13:41,264
We got into a fight because we wanted to go to different restaurants.

233
00:13:41,265 --> 00:13:43,499
Oh, The Bomun Lake Resort is good too. The scenery is pretty.

234
00:13:43,499 --> 00:13:46,431
Wow! That's a really nice place.

235
00:13:46,432 --> 00:13:47,965
I also went there with my wife.

236
00:13:47,966 --> 00:13:50,198
- What did you do there? 
 - We got into a fight

237
00:13:50,198 --> 00:13:51,800
because we wanted to see different things.

238
00:13:51,800 --> 00:13:54,565
Chief Editor. Please get along well with your wife.

239
00:13:54,565 --> 00:13:58,899
Studies show that domestic trouble can affect a child's grades in school.

240
00:13:58,900 --> 00:14:00,032
- Is it your kid? 
 - What?

241
00:14:00,033 --> 00:14:01,366
Leave my family out of it.

242
00:14:01,367 --> 00:14:03,232
- I was just worried... 
 - I said, leave them out of it!

243
00:14:03,232 --> 00:14:04,699
Stop!

244
00:14:04,699 --> 00:14:06,965
- Let's go somewhere else and talk. 
 - Okay.

245
00:14:06,965 --> 00:14:09,332
- Not you. I meant Editor Nam. 
 - What?

246
00:14:09,332 --> 00:14:11,465
You're only hindering the conversation.

247
00:14:11,465 --> 00:14:13,699
- Let's go, Editor Nam. 
 - Okay.

248
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:17,099
- I'll buy you a cup of coffee. 
 - Okay. Thank you.

249
00:14:20,799 --> 00:14:22,666
I'm lonely.

250
00:14:23,432 --> 00:14:25,366
So lonely.

251
00:14:26,367 --> 00:14:29,899
Leaving home, I got on a deep-sea fishing vessel

252
00:14:29,900 --> 00:14:31,598
and got injured.

253
00:14:31,599 --> 00:14:34,100
So I was kicked out.

254
00:14:34,100 --> 00:14:35,733
Were you hurt badly?

255
00:14:35,734 --> 00:14:38,266
Are you okay now?

256
00:14:38,266 --> 00:14:40,000
Since I left like that,

257
00:14:40,000 --> 00:14:44,333
I was so ashamed that I couldn't return home.

258
00:14:45,132 --> 00:14:47,165
- I'm so sorry. 
 - Bull crap.

259
00:14:47,165 --> 00:14:49,631
You were hiding from the creditors.

260
00:14:49,632 --> 00:14:51,032
To live comfortably by yourself.

261
00:14:51,033 --> 00:14:53,399
No, I really

262
00:14:53,400 --> 00:14:55,298
tried to earn money

263
00:14:55,298 --> 00:14:57,600
to pay off the debt somehow and come find you.

264
00:14:57,600 --> 00:15:00,499
I also did everything here that would make money

265
00:15:00,500 --> 00:15:01,998
and saved up.

266
00:15:01,998 --> 00:15:03,799
You must've suffered so much alone.

267
00:15:03,799 --> 00:15:05,366
What load of crap.

268
00:15:05,367 --> 00:15:06,631
Suffer so much alone?

269
00:15:06,632 --> 00:15:08,165
You suffered a million times more.

270
00:15:08,166 --> 00:15:10,064
- Mom... 
 - What?

271
00:15:10,064 --> 00:15:12,999
She never stopped working while she was in college.

272
00:15:13,000 --> 00:15:14,264
She got a job right after graduation

273
00:15:14,265 --> 00:15:16,264
and paid our debt off with every paycheck.

274
00:15:16,265 --> 00:15:18,399
She worked night and day.

275
00:15:18,400 --> 00:15:19,932
I'm sorry.

276
00:15:20,566 --> 00:15:24,166
What I did was very wrong.

277
00:15:24,166 --> 00:15:26,267
At least you know that.

278
00:15:27,432 --> 00:15:28,467
Forget it.

279
00:15:28,467 --> 00:15:30,264
Get up. We're leaving.

280
00:15:30,265 --> 00:15:33,733
Let's take Dad, all right?

281
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:37,300
No. How can I?

282
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:38,834
I'm not without conscience.

283
00:15:38,834 --> 00:15:41,798
- Mom. 
 - Don't worry about me.

284
00:15:41,799 --> 00:15:44,167
- Go. 
 - Pack your bags.

285
00:15:44,167 --> 00:15:46,933
What if Young Won gets married?

286
00:15:46,934 --> 00:15:49,332
- Will you greet your son-in-law like that? 
 - Honey...

287
00:15:49,332 --> 00:15:51,465
I can't let that happen.

288
00:15:51,466 --> 00:15:52,933
Pack your bags and follow us.

289
00:15:52,934 --> 00:15:54,534
Now.

290
00:15:56,734 --> 00:15:57,899
Let's go.

291
00:15:57,899 --> 00:15:59,366
Okay.

292
00:16:00,232 --> 00:16:02,098
Come in.

293
00:16:02,099 --> 00:16:05,367
This is the office that your son works in.

294
00:16:06,867 --> 00:16:08,800
- Who are they? 
 - Oh?

295
00:16:09,466 --> 00:16:13,199
I don't know. They look familiar...

296
00:16:13,833 --> 00:16:16,366
- Mom? 
 - Dad!

297
00:16:16,366 --> 00:16:18,499
- What? 
 - You can stand here.

298
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:20,032
Hello.

299
00:16:20,033 --> 00:16:21,933
- Oh, hello. 
 - Hello.

300
00:16:21,933 --> 00:16:23,333
What brings you here?

301
00:16:23,333 --> 00:16:25,566
They were worried you were skipping meals,

302
00:16:25,566 --> 00:16:27,631
so they came here themselves to see you.

303
00:16:27,632 --> 00:16:29,899
Because you've been working overtime every day

304
00:16:29,900 --> 00:16:32,765
instead of going home.

305
00:16:38,833 --> 00:16:40,431
Your cooking is superb.

306
00:16:40,432 --> 00:16:43,267
This is so delicious, Ma'am.

307
00:16:43,267 --> 00:16:46,432
Oh, thank you.

308
00:16:46,432 --> 00:16:47,733
Chief Editor.

309
00:16:47,734 --> 00:16:49,899
Please excuse me for saying this...

310
00:16:49,900 --> 00:16:52,298
Oh, please go ahead.

311
00:16:52,299 --> 00:16:54,298
I know there's much work to do,

312
00:16:54,299 --> 00:16:59,399
but can you at least let my son sleep at home?

313
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:02,034
- Excuse me? 
 - Dad, please!

314
00:17:02,034 --> 00:17:05,098
What? When you don't come home, your mother doesn't sleep well.

315
00:17:05,099 --> 00:17:07,065
Do you know how worried she gets?

316
00:17:07,066 --> 00:17:08,299
Honey.

317
00:17:08,300 --> 00:17:10,132
Don't say that.

318
00:17:10,133 --> 00:17:12,866
Oh, yes, of course.

319
00:17:12,866 --> 00:17:13,899
You heard your father, right?

320
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:17,498
Starting from today, go home. Every day.

321
00:17:17,498 --> 00:17:18,867
Yes, sir.

322
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:23,232
By the way, our Sang Soon must get married soon.

323
00:17:23,232 --> 00:17:24,799
Editor Yeo, you're the same age as him.

324
00:17:24,800 --> 00:17:28,032
If you know a good woman, can you introduce her to him?

325
00:17:28,032 --> 00:17:30,033
Pardon?

326
00:17:30,033 --> 00:17:32,067
Oh, sure.

327
00:17:32,133 --> 00:17:34,100
Stop talking about things like that here.

328
00:17:34,100 --> 00:17:36,365
Finish eating and leave. I have to go cover a story.

329
00:17:36,366 --> 00:17:37,999
You know why we're saying this!

330
00:17:37,999 --> 00:17:39,499
You have to get married soon

331
00:17:39,500 --> 00:17:41,065
and give us grandchildren...

332
00:17:41,066 --> 00:17:43,099
I'm not getting married!

333
00:17:43,699 --> 00:17:44,332
- What? 
 - What?

334
00:17:44,333 --> 00:17:45,264
I'm against marriage.

335
00:17:45,265 --> 00:17:47,533
I loathe marriage!

336
00:17:48,799 --> 00:17:50,299
You bastard!

337
00:17:50,300 --> 00:17:52,967
How can you say that to your parents?

338
00:17:52,967 --> 00:17:56,266
Do you want to see your mother collapse?

339
00:18:09,265 --> 00:18:11,599
- Are you okay? 
 - Yes.

340
00:18:14,300 --> 00:18:17,167
They want it so badly.

341
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:21,299
Why don't you reconsider marriage?

342
00:18:21,300 --> 00:18:23,932
Yes, I think I should.

343
00:18:23,933 --> 00:18:25,633
Right?

344
00:18:25,633 --> 00:18:27,099
I'm glad you think so.

345
00:18:27,099 --> 00:18:29,198
Marriage isn't such a bad thing...

346
00:18:29,199 --> 00:18:31,098
My relationship with him...

347
00:18:31,099 --> 00:18:33,565
- I need to reconsider it. 
 - What?

348
00:18:33,565 --> 00:18:34,932
I have no intention of marrying.

349
00:18:34,933 --> 00:18:36,899
So holding Sang Soon back

350
00:18:36,900 --> 00:18:38,065
is an awful thing to do.

351
00:18:38,066 --> 00:18:39,299
Wait, Editor Yeo...

352
00:18:39,300 --> 00:18:42,098
My parents are leaving.

353
00:18:42,098 --> 00:18:44,932
Okay, we'll be there.

354
00:18:46,833 --> 00:18:49,932
You're not going to break up right away, right?

355
00:18:49,933 --> 00:18:52,599
- Right? 
 - Let's go say goodbye.

356
00:19:03,233 --> 00:19:06,298
Why did you bring all your worn out clothes?

357
00:19:06,298 --> 00:19:09,800
Throw this away. This, too.

358
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:12,566
- Mom. 
 - What?

359
00:19:12,567 --> 00:19:14,365
Man of nature?

360
00:19:14,366 --> 00:19:15,499
What a laugh!

361
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,033
You're a jobless guy living in the mountain.

362
00:19:17,033 --> 00:19:19,765
- Stop it. 
 - It's okay.

363
00:19:19,766 --> 00:19:22,933
