406
00:21:19,866 --> 00:21:21,232
Look.

407
00:21:21,233 --> 00:21:23,098
Hold your arm up firmly.

408
00:21:23,099 --> 00:21:25,567
Don't move.

409
00:21:25,567 --> 00:21:27,765
Make it level with the person.

410
00:21:27,766 --> 00:21:29,999
That way, the composition is stable.

411
00:21:30,000 --> 00:21:32,632
It's important to make it level...

412
00:21:32,633 --> 00:21:36,199
with the person...

413
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,366
What's with the smirk?

414
00:21:41,366 --> 00:21:42,899
It's good to see you like this.

415
00:21:42,899 --> 00:21:44,098
Like what?

416
00:21:44,099 --> 00:21:46,800
It's nice to see you happy.

417
00:21:50,500 --> 00:21:52,265
It's all thanks to you.

418
00:21:52,265 --> 00:21:54,334
If it weren't for you,

419
00:21:55,733 --> 00:21:58,599
the me of today wouldn't exist.

420
00:22:07,366 --> 00:22:09,466
 Come on, let's eat.

421
00:22:09,467 --> 00:22:11,199
 Eat up and get energy.

422
00:22:11,199 --> 00:22:12,264
 I'm okay.

423
00:22:12,265 --> 00:22:14,031
 Don't say that.

424
00:22:14,032 --> 00:22:17,565
 I asked my wife to pack a lot, so I can share with you.

425
00:22:17,565 --> 00:22:20,933
 If there are leftovers, my wife will scold me.

426
00:22:20,933 --> 00:22:24,200
 Did you get the money you needed?

427
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:26,800
 No.

428
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:29,598
 I borrowed money from people and got a bank loan.

429
00:22:29,599 --> 00:22:31,733
 But it's still not enough.

430
00:22:32,599 --> 00:22:35,733
 I've been meaning to ask. Do you...

431
00:22:35,733 --> 00:22:37,899
 Never mind.

432
00:22:37,899 --> 00:22:40,132
 I shouldn't ask.

433
00:22:40,132 --> 00:22:42,500
 I'll lend you the money.

434
00:22:44,032 --> 00:22:48,433
 You always told me that your wish is to become a homeowner

435
00:22:48,433 --> 00:22:51,233
 and live with your family with no worries about having to move.

436
00:22:51,233 --> 00:22:53,866
 You always treat me like a son,

437
00:22:53,866 --> 00:22:55,565
 so I'm repaying you.

438
00:22:55,565 --> 00:22:59,831
 I will never forget your kindness.

439
00:22:59,831 --> 00:23:01,931
 I'll pay you back first thing.

440
00:23:01,931 --> 00:23:04,432
 - Thank you, Ja Sung. 
 - Sure.

441
00:23:05,734 --> 00:23:08,233
 - Let's eat. 
 - Thank you!

442
00:23:08,233 --> 00:23:09,598
 Oh, Ja Sung.

443
00:23:09,599 --> 00:23:10,765
 Did you hear?

444
00:23:10,766 --> 00:23:12,932
 - Mr. Na has gone off the grid. 
 - What?

445
00:23:12,932 --> 00:23:16,899
 He borrowed money from people and fled.

446
00:23:42,866 --> 00:23:47,067
If you hadn't been by my side, comforting me,

447
00:23:48,300 --> 00:23:50,532
it would've been really hard for me.

448
00:23:50,532 --> 00:23:53,434
You're so grateful, right?

449
00:23:53,434 --> 00:23:56,732
Then forget that gloomy past,

450
00:23:56,732 --> 00:23:59,533
and think only about a bright, happy future.

451
00:23:59,533 --> 00:24:02,833
Okay. Thanks.

452
00:24:03,599 --> 00:24:07,032
- What are you doing? Set the composition again. 
 - Okay.

453
00:24:07,032 --> 00:24:10,000
- Grip it tight. 
 - Real tight.

454
00:24:27,133 --> 00:24:28,799
Ui Joo!

455
00:24:28,800 --> 00:24:30,399
- There you are. 
 - Yeah.

456
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:31,865
What are you doing?

457
00:24:31,866 --> 00:24:33,132
What do you think?

458
00:24:33,133 --> 00:24:34,999
I'm working.

459
00:24:37,032 --> 00:24:40,431
Don't worry about what my parents said.

460
00:24:40,431 --> 00:24:43,233
I really have no intention of getting married.

461
00:24:46,599 --> 00:24:49,032
Joo! Let's go straight home after work.

462
00:24:49,032 --> 00:24:50,698
I'll make you dinner.

463
00:24:50,699 --> 00:24:52,865
I'll cook truffle pasta that you like and...

464
00:24:52,866 --> 00:24:55,399
Go to your home today.

465
00:24:55,400 --> 00:24:57,666
Your parents will worry.

466
00:24:58,300 --> 00:25:00,666
- No, it's okay. 
 - It's because I'm tired.

467
00:25:00,666 --> 00:25:02,399
I want to rest alone.

468
00:25:02,399 --> 00:25:05,166
Oh, okay.

469
00:25:05,166 --> 00:25:08,399
- I'll be going now. 
 - Bye.

470
00:25:19,866 --> 00:25:22,166
What am I going to do?

471
00:25:34,140 --> 00:25:35,860

472
00:25:35,860 --> 00:25:39,864
You take a trip to learn.

473
00:25:43,567 --> 00:25:46,266
Is that so?

474
00:25:52,999 --> 00:25:55,366
Oh, look at the time!

475
00:25:55,366 --> 00:25:58,032
Has Young Won come back to Seoul?

476
00:26:00,666 --> 00:26:03,198
 Did you get home safe?

477
00:26:03,199 --> 00:26:06,032
 Are you sure it wasn't anything bad?

478
00:26:06,032 --> 00:26:08,966
 Yes, it was no big deal.

479
00:26:08,967 --> 00:26:11,999
 Won't you be tired for tomorrow's trip?

480
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:13,365
 Get some sleep.

481
00:26:13,366 --> 00:26:15,666
 You, too.

482
00:26:19,166 --> 00:26:23,498
 So this is how it feels not to be able to sleep before a trip.

483
00:26:23,498 --> 00:26:25,765
 My heart is fluttering. I'm looking forward to it,

484
00:26:25,766 --> 00:26:28,466
 so much I don't think I'll be able to sleep.

485
00:26:43,366 --> 00:26:47,165
 I also lost all the money I saved up once.

486
00:26:47,166 --> 00:26:49,566
 I was betrayed by someone I trusted.

487
00:26:49,567 --> 00:26:53,200
 It was the biggest ordeal and scar of my life.

488
00:26:53,200 --> 00:26:55,899
 I thought it was no use trying to make it.

489
00:26:55,900 --> 00:26:57,799
 The pain was unimaginable.

490
00:26:57,800 --> 00:26:59,598
 I wanted to die.

491
00:26:59,599 --> 00:27:03,865
 After that, he built a wall around himself and lived a lonely life,

492
00:27:03,865 --> 00:27:05,332
 only focused on making money.

493
00:27:05,333 --> 00:27:06,733
 I always worked part-time at night,

494
00:27:06,734 --> 00:27:09,633
 so I haven't been on a school trip.

495
00:27:14,567 --> 00:27:16,733
 My heart is fluttering, too.

496
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:20,399
 Let's have fun on our trip.

497
00:27:20,399 --> 00:27:23,232
 Make it a trip we'll never forget.

498
00:28:00,300 --> 00:28:01,967
Ja Sung.

499
00:28:01,967 --> 00:28:04,800
- Get in. 
 - Okay.

500
00:28:05,567 --> 00:28:08,465
Oh, no. It's locked.

