00:30:23,467 --> 00:30:25,633
Oh? The lights are on.

545
00:30:25,633 --> 00:30:27,399
Oh? Chief Editor.

546
00:30:27,400 --> 00:30:30,298
Hey. Why'd you come to work on the weekend?

547
00:30:30,298 --> 00:30:33,267
Oh. I have some work left.

548
00:30:33,267 --> 00:30:38,398
Jeez. It's because you leave on the dot to go to Editor Yeo's house.

549
00:30:38,398 --> 00:30:40,899
I'll be reprimanded by your parents again.

550
00:30:40,900 --> 00:30:43,665
Since I'm calling you out on the weekend to work.

551
00:30:43,665 --> 00:30:45,833
Well, then.

552
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:47,932
Let's go out and get some drinks...

553
00:30:47,932 --> 00:30:51,432
No. I'm going to finish up and go on a date.

554
00:30:51,432 --> 00:30:53,665
Jeez. Okay, then.

555
00:30:53,665 --> 00:30:56,832
Do you think I don't have anyone else to drink with?

556
00:30:56,832 --> 00:30:59,233
What a lousy friend.

557
00:31:01,367 --> 00:31:03,733
Hello, sir.

558
00:31:03,733 --> 00:31:05,632
It's the weekend. What are you doing?

559
00:31:05,633 --> 00:31:07,065
How about a drink...?

560
00:31:07,066 --> 00:31:09,132
He... Hello?

561
00:31:10,567 --> 00:31:12,967
He hung up on me.

562
00:31:13,666 --> 00:31:15,632
Hi, Joo.

563
00:31:15,633 --> 00:31:17,132
I'm almost done.

564
00:31:17,132 --> 00:31:19,600
What should we do? Watch a movie?

565
00:31:20,500 --> 00:31:23,065
No. I'm tired.

566
00:31:23,066 --> 00:31:25,065
I want to stay home.

567
00:31:25,065 --> 00:31:27,032
Really?

568
00:31:27,032 --> 00:31:29,898
Then I'll come and cook for you. The pasta I promised yesterday.

569
00:31:29,898 --> 00:31:32,199
No. I want to be alone.

570
00:31:32,199 --> 00:31:33,399
I'm tired.

571
00:31:33,399 --> 00:31:34,732
Are you really tired?

572
00:31:34,732 --> 00:31:36,164
Or are you avoiding me?

573
00:31:36,164 --> 00:31:38,265
- What? 
 - Why...

574
00:31:38,265 --> 00:31:40,699
- Are you avoiding me? 
 - I'm not avoiding you.

575
00:31:40,699 --> 00:31:42,765
You've been avoiding me since yesterday

576
00:31:42,765 --> 00:31:46,000
after you met my parents.

577
00:31:48,032 --> 00:31:49,566
I'll come to your place.

578
00:31:49,567 --> 00:31:52,332
Let's talk face to face.

579
00:31:56,366 --> 00:31:58,100
Okay.

580
00:31:58,100 --> 00:32:00,466
I should tell him.

581
00:32:00,466 --> 00:32:02,334
I'll tell him.

582
00:32:04,320 --> 00:32:10,300
♫  You’re my love  ♫

583
00:32:10,300 --> 00:32:12,560
Let's go, Student Na Young Won.

584
00:32:12,560 --> 00:32:15,267
♫  Look at me, I’ll be standing right here  ♫

585
00:32:15,267 --> 00:32:20,830
♫  Hey, I feel that I’ve changed because of you  ♫

586
00:32:20,830 --> 00:32:23,190
♫  Sometimes I feel like I’m day dreaming  ♫

587
00:32:23,190 --> 00:32:25,533
Here we go.

588
00:32:25,533 --> 00:32:28,060
♫  Whatever it is, I’ll do it for you  ♫

589
00:32:28,060 --> 00:32:29,730
♫  Whenever you need someone on your side  ♫

590
00:32:29,734 --> 00:32:34,732
Student Na Young Won.

591
00:32:34,732 --> 00:32:35,730
♫  Don’t mind  ♫

592
00:32:35,730 --> 00:32:38,200
♫  So you won’t think that you’re alone  ♫

593
00:32:38,200 --> 00:32:40,450
♫  I’ll hold your hands and open your ears  ♫

594
00:32:40,450 --> 00:32:42,300
♫  I’m there,  ♫

595
00:32:42,300 --> 00:32:46,465
I didn't know there was a place that lent school uniforms.

596
00:32:46,465 --> 00:32:51,565
Wearing this, it truly feels like a school trip.

597
00:32:51,565 --> 00:32:55,100
Now I don't feel sad about never having gone on a school trip.

598
00:32:55,100 --> 00:32:57,760
♫  You’re my love  ♫

599
00:32:57,760 --> 00:32:59,566
Since I've met you,

600
00:32:59,567 --> 00:33:05,020
I feel like the holes in my life are filled completely.

601
00:33:12,467 --> 00:33:14,233
Let's wrap up Hwangridan Road.

602
00:33:14,233 --> 00:33:16,600
- The next plan... 
 - Wait...

603
00:33:16,600 --> 00:33:18,598
Can we go back to our lodging?

604
00:33:18,599 --> 00:33:20,665
What? Already?

605
00:33:20,666 --> 00:33:22,665
There's so much left to see.

606
00:33:22,666 --> 00:33:24,599
We need to see Woljeonggyo Bridge and Bulguksa Temple.

607
00:33:24,599 --> 00:33:27,933
There's something I want to do, too.

608
00:33:37,500 --> 00:33:41,266
Ui Joo. I really have no intention of getting married...

609
00:33:41,266 --> 00:33:43,331
Can you hear me out first?

610
00:33:43,331 --> 00:33:45,366
I have something to say, too.

611
00:33:45,366 --> 00:33:48,366
That's why I didn't stop you from coming.

612
00:33:49,500 --> 00:33:53,499
- Sang Soon, let's... 
 - No.

613
00:33:53,500 --> 00:33:56,098
I know what you're going to say, but my answer is no.

614
00:33:56,098 --> 00:33:58,665
I'm not breaking up with you ever.

615
00:33:58,665 --> 00:33:59,699
No, I can't.

616
00:33:59,699 --> 00:34:00,899
What?

617
00:34:00,899 --> 00:34:05,766
I don't have to get married.

618
00:34:05,766 --> 00:34:08,999
I can live alone my whole life.

619
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:12,699
Just let me be by your side like this. Is that so hard?

620
00:34:12,699 --> 00:34:15,967
Yes, it's hard.

621
00:34:17,300 --> 00:34:18,632
Let's stop dating.

622
00:34:18,633 --> 00:34:19,798
How can you...

623
00:34:19,798 --> 00:34:21,931
Let's stop dating and get married.

624
00:34:21,931 --> 00:34:25,299
- What? 
 - Let's get married.

625
00:34:25,299 --> 00:34:26,933
No.

626
00:34:28,333 --> 00:34:31,665
Please marry me, Sang Soon.

627
00:34:36,100 --> 00:34:39,566
It might seem sudden,

628
00:34:39,566 --> 00:34:43,399
but I have thought about it a lot since yesterday.

629
00:34:44,065 --> 00:34:45,698
But...

630
00:34:45,699 --> 00:34:47,699
 Thank you for the food.

631
00:34:47,699 --> 00:34:49,432
 You're most welcome.

632
00:34:49,433 --> 00:34:52,367
 Then we'll be going now.

633
00:34:52,367 --> 00:34:54,799
 - Goodbye. 
 - Goodbye.

634
00:34:54,800 --> 00:34:58,133
 - I'll go cover my story. 
 - Okay.

635
00:34:58,133 --> 00:34:59,666
 Let's go.

636
00:35:01,533 --> 00:35:03,866
 Let's go inside.

637
00:35:03,866 --> 00:35:05,265
 I need to go.

638
00:35:05,266 --> 00:35:07,899
 Your shoelace came undone.

639
00:35:13,333 --> 00:35:15,133
 All done.

640
00:35:15,133 --> 00:35:18,233
 Be careful, be careful.

641
00:35:18,233 --> 00:35:21,599
 Watch your head. Watch your head.

642
00:35:26,533 --> 00:35:30,031
A son learns from his father.

643
00:35:30,032 --> 00:35:34,800
Seeing him be so sweet to his wife even at his age,

644
00:35:34,833 --> 00:35:37,964
I felt that I could trust you.

645
00:35:37,964 --> 00:35:41,031
You're not breaking up because of my parents,

646
00:35:41,032 --> 00:35:44,332
but because of them, you want to get married?

647
00:35:44,333 --> 00:35:51,165
I would feel moved thinking there couldn't be anyone sweeter

648
00:35:51,967 --> 00:35:54,166
or warmer than you,

649
00:35:54,166 --> 00:35:56,198
but then I'd think men are all the same.

650
00:35:56,199 --> 00:36:01,366
That you could betray me like my father did.

651
00:36:03,199 --> 00:36:07,400
But now I feel like you might be different from the rest.

652
00:36:08,200 --> 00:36:10,166
Ui Joo.

653
00:36:15,733 --> 00:36:19,933
Will you marry me?

654
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:27,000
Of course!

655
00:36:29,733 --> 00:36:35,398
I promise. I'll treat you better than my dad treats my mom.

656
00:36:44,166 --> 00:36:46,099
I'll be good to you.

657
00:36:55,366 --> 00:36:57,367
Welcome.

658
00:36:59,599 --> 00:37:00,732
Excuse me.

659
00:37:00,733 --> 00:37:04,300
- One pork belly and a bottle of soju, please. 
 - Okay.

660
00:37:06,333 --> 00:37:07,933
What?

661
00:37:07,933 --> 00:37:10,066
Secretary Hwang!

662
00:37:11,065 --> 00:37:15,866
Jeez. It must be so hard assisting CEO Yoo.

663
00:37:15,866 --> 00:37:18,832
No wonder you're here for a drink on a weekend.

664
00:37:18,833 --> 00:37:20,265
I'm not here to drink.

665
00:37:20,266 --> 00:37:24,299
- I'm here to eat... 
 - I know how you feel.

666
00:37:24,300 --> 00:37:27,231
You don't need to hide it from me.

667
00:37:27,232 --> 00:37:29,531
CEO Yoo is so picky.

668
00:37:29,532 --> 00:37:31,698
He's also fickle.

669
00:37:31,699 --> 00:37:33,499
He's not fickle. He's cautious.

670
00:37:33,499 --> 00:37:38,698
Come on. You don't have to hide your true feelings from me.

671
00:37:38,699 --> 00:37:41,099
They say a widower knows how a widow feels.

672
00:37:41,100 --> 00:37:44,732
I'm in the same position as you.

673
00:37:44,732 --> 00:37:47,200
Oh, sure.

674
00:37:47,200 --> 00:37:48,565
Excuse me.

675
00:37:48,566 --> 00:37:50,599
- I have to go. I have something to do. 
 - Okay.

676
00:37:50,600 --> 00:37:52,965
- I got this. 
 - No way.

677
00:37:52,965 --> 00:37:55,299
Knowing CEO Yoo, I bet you're paid very little.

678
00:37:55,300 --> 00:37:57,565
It's fine. I'll pay.

679
00:37:57,566 --> 00:38:00,632
Excuse me. Check, please.

680
00:38:06,333 --> 00:38:08,165
- Thank you. 
 - Sure.

681
00:38:08,165 --> 00:38:13,366
Make a lot of money and get away from CEO Yoo.

682
00:38:13,366 --> 00:38:15,832
Okay. Bye.

683
00:38:15,832 --> 00:38:18,232
Oh, my. Are you already leaving?

684
00:38:18,232 --> 00:38:20,733
I was going to give you more meat, on the house.

685
00:38:20,733 --> 00:38:22,466
Are you a regular here?

686
00:38:22,466 --> 00:38:24,398
Oh, you didn't know?

687
00:38:24,399 --> 00:38:27,533
- He owns this building. 
 - What?

688
00:38:27,533 --> 00:38:31,398
He lowered the rent because times are tough.

689
00:38:31,398 --> 00:38:34,898
He was even awarded "Good Landlord" from the borough office.

690
00:38:34,899 --> 00:38:38,332
He's still young, but he's amazing.

691
00:38:38,333 --> 00:38:40,099
- Excuse me. 
 - Yes?

692
00:38:40,100 --> 00:38:42,332
See you next time.

693
00:38:42,333 --> 00:38:44,100
What can I do for you?

694
00:38:45,866 --> 00:38:47,165
What the...?

695
00:38:47,166 --> 00:38:50,065
- Are you from a rich family? 
 - Oh, no.

696
00:38:50,065 --> 00:38:52,432
Then how can you own a building at your age?

697
00:38:52,433 --> 00:38:53,665
What's your secret?

698
00:38:53,666 --> 00:38:56,398
They say a dog recites a poem if it spends three years at a village school.

699
00:38:56,399 --> 00:38:59,400
I learned about real estate by watching CEO Yoo.

700
00:38:59,400 --> 00:39:04,899
I guess my secret is finding things to learn about instead of complaining.

701
00:39:04,899 --> 00:39:07,600
I'm busy, so I'll be going now.

702
00:39:11,733 --> 00:39:13,532
Oh, okay.

703
00:39:13,532 --> 00:39:15,100

704
00:39:15,100 --> 00:39:17,566
₩123,000 ($123).

705
00:39:17,566 --> 00:39:19,132
Wait, Secretary Hwang.

706
00:39:19,133 --> 00:39:20,732
Hey, Building Owner!

707
00:39:20,733 --> 00:39:22,765
You pay for this!

708
00:39:26,399 --> 00:39:29,032
Oh, is this what you wanted to do?

709
00:39:29,032 --> 00:39:30,265
Yes.

710
00:39:30,266 --> 00:39:34,799
I wanted to be with you alone.

711
00:39:37,133 --> 00:39:39,000
I'm sorry.

712
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:42,534
I read in a book that you take a trip to learn.

713
00:39:42,566 --> 00:39:46,533
I wanted to show you as many sites as I could

714
00:39:46,533 --> 00:39:48,632
and pushed my plans onto you.

715
00:39:48,633 --> 00:39:52,532
It's okay. That was good, too.

716
00:39:52,532 --> 00:39:55,000
But you take a trip

717
00:39:56,233 --> 00:39:59,933
also to make good memories.

718
00:40:02,932 --> 00:40:07,432
From now on, let's go on a lot of trips.

719
00:40:07,432 --> 00:40:10,060
Let's make a lot of good memories.

720
00:40:39,299 --> 00:40:40,732
You must be tired.

721
00:40:40,732 --> 00:40:42,798
Go inside and rest.

722
00:40:42,798 --> 00:40:43,964
No.

723
00:40:43,964 --> 00:40:46,265
Come up with me.

724
00:40:46,265 --> 00:40:47,899
Can I do that?

725
00:40:47,899 --> 00:40:52,633
I really wanted to, but I held back.

726
00:40:53,766 --> 00:40:56,799
There's something I didn't tell you.

727
00:40:56,799 --> 00:40:58,431
I actually found my dad.

728
00:40:58,431 --> 00:41:00,465
What? Really?

729
00:41:00,465 --> 00:41:02,165
Why didn't you tell me?

730
00:41:02,165 --> 00:41:04,833
I wanted our trip to be a happy memory for you.

731
00:41:04,833 --> 00:41:06,000
What do you mean...?

732
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:10,067
My dad is going to come by to see you.

733
00:41:10,067 --> 00:41:13,199
So suddenly?

734
00:41:13,199 --> 00:41:15,198
Let me go home and change—

735
00:41:15,199 --> 00:41:17,032
Ja Sung.

736
00:41:25,967 --> 00:41:27,899
Mr. Na...

737
00:41:33,066 --> 00:41:34,733
I'm sorry.

738
00:41:36,965 --> 00:41:40,520
I'm so sorry, Ja Sung.

739
00:42:01,232 --> 00:42:03,365
- Where are you? 
  - Home.

740
00:42:03,365 --> 00:42:06,766
- Let's go camping. 
 - No, no.

741
00:42:06,766 --> 00:42:08,765
Why not? You have nothing else to do.

742
00:42:08,765 --> 00:42:10,265
 No, no, no, no.

743
00:42:10,265 --> 00:42:12,899
I'm tired. Bye.

744
00:42:15,633 --> 00:42:18,200
You really don't have to go?

745
00:42:19,399 --> 00:42:20,598
No.

746
00:42:20,598 --> 00:42:24,166
But what brings you to my house?

747
00:42:26,232 --> 00:42:29,933
I packed you lunch. Help yourself.

748
00:42:29,933 --> 00:42:32,333
- What? 
 - I'm very grateful.

749
00:42:32,333 --> 00:42:35,366
You carried me on your back and took me home.

750
00:42:35,366 --> 00:42:38,131
I hesitated how to express my thanks.

751
00:42:38,131 --> 00:42:39,565
I'm only now expressing it like this.

752
00:42:39,565 --> 00:42:41,098
Oh, well.

753
00:42:41,098 --> 00:42:44,067
I did what should've been done.

754
00:42:49,366 --> 00:42:51,733
Wow, awesome!

755
00:42:51,733 --> 00:42:55,132
You made this for me?

756
00:42:55,132 --> 00:42:56,000
Yes.

757
00:42:56,000 --> 00:42:58,964
Not for someone else? For me?

758
00:42:58,964 --> 00:43:01,133
Of course.

759
00:43:01,133 --> 00:43:02,233
I hope you enjoy it!

760
00:43:02,233 --> 00:43:04,367
I'll be going now.

761
00:43:05,366 --> 00:43:07,267
Wait, Mi Ra.

762
00:43:07,267 --> 00:43:08,766
Yes?

763
00:43:08,766 --> 00:43:12,767
If you haven't had lunch, would you like to join me?

764
00:43:17,799 --> 00:43:20,265
I'm so glad you reunited with your father.

765
00:43:20,265 --> 00:43:23,366
Let's meet him often and...

766
00:43:25,333 --> 00:43:27,698
This is the money my dad saved up until now.

767
00:43:27,698 --> 00:43:31,500
I'll send you the rest once my mom's store is sold.

768
00:43:31,500 --> 00:43:33,065
You don't have to do this.

769
00:43:33,065 --> 00:43:37,331
If it weren't for that time, I wouldn't have succeeded like this.

770
00:43:37,331 --> 00:43:38,799
No.

771
00:43:38,799 --> 00:43:44,967
If it weren't for that time, you wouldn't have suffered in pain.

772
00:43:44,967 --> 00:43:48,299
It's okay. It's all water under the bridge.

773
00:43:48,299 --> 00:43:50,567
Let's end this.

774
00:43:51,299 --> 00:43:53,266
What?

775
00:43:53,266 --> 00:43:57,166
I know how much you suffered because of my dad.

776
00:43:58,266 --> 00:44:02,699
I'm not so shameless that I can stay with you after knowing all that.

777
00:44:02,699 --> 00:44:04,931
But it was my misunderstanding.

778
00:44:04,931 --> 00:44:07,931
All this time, I thought he purposely deceived me.

779
00:44:07,931 --> 00:44:09,531
But that wasn't the case.

780
00:44:09,531 --> 00:44:11,867
He was conned by his friend, so he had no choice—

781
00:44:11,867 --> 00:44:14,499
Even if he didn't have a choice,

782
00:44:14,499 --> 00:44:19,960
he shouldn't have disappeared on you like that.

783
00:44:19,960 --> 00:44:21,490
♫  The fights and the scars  ♫

784
00:44:21,490 --> 00:44:24,233
I am so scared

785
00:44:24,233 --> 00:44:28,466
about the fact that the suffering you went through,

786
00:44:28,466 --> 00:44:30,798
which made you want to die,

787
00:44:30,798 --> 00:44:32,866
was because of my dad.

788
00:44:32,866 --> 00:44:35,332
Don't worry. I can forget all of that.

789
00:44:35,333 --> 00:44:38,866
You'll only be making an effort to forget,

790
00:44:38,866 --> 00:44:42,966
but you'll be reminded of it when you look at me.

791
00:44:42,966 --> 00:44:44,930
Can you deny that?

792
00:44:44,930 --> 00:44:46,490
♫  I’m so lonely and you were my only light  ♫

793
00:44:46,490 --> 00:44:49,732
And I...

794
00:44:49,732 --> 00:44:54,300
I'll feel terrible and grieved when I look at you.

795
00:44:54,300 --> 00:44:56,199
Young Won.

796
00:44:56,199 --> 00:44:59,467
Don't do this. Please.

797
00:44:59,467 --> 00:45:01,667
I'm sorry.

798
00:45:01,667 --> 00:45:07,133
And thank you for everything.

799
00:45:07,133 --> 00:45:09,666
Don't do this.

800
00:45:09,666 --> 00:45:11,000
I need to, for myself.

801
00:45:11,000 --> 00:45:14,160
♫  And go next to you  ♫

802
00:45:14,160 --> 00:45:15,760
Let me go. For me.

803
00:45:15,760 --> 00:45:21,800
♫  Because I think I can forget all the painful times  ♫

804
00:45:21,800 --> 00:45:29,630
♫  I’m looking for you like this  ♫

805
00:45:30,630 --> 00:45:35,960
♫  But where are you?  ♫

806
00:45:35,960 --> 00:45:40,900
